FBIS3-13192 "drnes047_s_94005" FBIS-NES-94-047 Document Type:Daily Report 10 Mar 1994 Iran Velayati, Afghanistan's Gaylani Meet, Discuss Events LD0903173394 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network in Persian 1630 GMT 9 Mar 94 LD0903173394 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network Language: Persian Article Type:BFN [Text] Mr. Pir Sayyed Ahmad Gaylani, the leader of the Mahaz-e Meli-ye Eslami-ye [National Islamic Front] of Afghanistan, met Foreign Affairs Minister 'Ali Akbar Velayati this afternoon. He announced his party's stance on the civil war in Kabul and described the situation in Afghanistan as critical. Mr. Gaylani also thanked the Islamic Republic of Iran for its efforts toward ending the war and establishing peace and stability in Afghanistan and the dispatch of humanitarian aid to the Muslim people of Afghanistan. Mr. Velayati expressed concern about the situation in Afghanistan and said: The Islamic Republic of Iran will not spare any assistance that will bring peace and tranquillity to Afghanistan and end the clashes and war in that country.
